<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-80-0639 </DOCNO><TEXT>A simple model was used to predict combat induced fires of flammable components(except ammunition) carried on combat vehicles. Five U.S. Army groundvehicles were examined. Eight attacking weapons were considered. Fueltemperatures from 8 to 53 C were included. The model was based as muchas possible on existing data which simply did not cover all situationsof interest. Considerable personal judgment was required. Nevertheless,the importance of certain vehicle properties include engine design, fuel-celllocation, vehicle material, and the presence of an automatic fire-suppressionsystem.</TEXT></DOC>